    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Oligopeptide-22 SP is a single chain human peptide produced synthetically to be identical to a portion of the protein, C-C Motif Chemokine 25, and contains 23 amino acids consisting of alanine, arginine, asparagine, aspartic acid, cysteine, glutamic acid, glutamine, glycine, histidine, leucine, lysine, methionine and proline. The parent protein contains a maximum of 150 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
